👉 Thread Priorities

public class Thread_Priorities {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        /* working of JVM : it holds a ready queue containing multiple threads 
                                        JVM manage this Threads
                                        Now , We can arrange the priorities of Threads
                                        We can give three types of priority to Threads in JAVA
        *               1. java.lang.Thread.MIN_PRIORITY = 1
        *               2. java.lang.Thread.NORM_PRIORITY = 5
        *               3. java.lang.Thread.MAX_PRIORITY = 10
        * These values are passed into Thread.setPriority(int) to assign priority to JAVA threads. */
    }
}

+-------------------+
| Before Priorities | --- Given as MAX to t1 thread , by default JAVA has normal priorities
